        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1990-10-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1990-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <head>164. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_SB_1">Scowcroft</persName>) to President Bush<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d164fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_BGHW_1"
                            >George H.W. Bush</persName> Library, <persName corresp="#p_BGHW_1"
                            >Bush</persName> Presidential Records, National Security Council,
                        H-Files, NSD Files, OA/ID 90004–026, NSD–50—October 12, 1990—Decisions on
                            <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CFE_1"
                            >CFE</gloss> Issues. Secret. Copied to Quayle and <persName
                            corresp="#p_SJH_1">Sununu</persName>. A stamped notation indicates
                            <persName corresp="#p_BGHW_1">Bush</persName> saw the memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1990-10-12">October 12, 1990</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>National Security Directive on <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>
                        and <gloss target="#t_CFE_1">CFE</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Purpose</p>
                <p>To seek your approval of a proposed National Security Directive providing revised
                    U.S. positions on several <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_CFE_1">CFE</gloss> issues.</p>
                <pb facs="0920" n="893" xml:id="pg_893"/>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Background</p>
                <p>I reviewed the major issues that remain in <gloss target="#t_START_1"
                        >START</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CFE_1">CFE</gloss> with <persName
                        corresp="#p_BJA_1">Jim Baker</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CRB_1">Dick
                        Cheney</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_PCL_1">Colin Powell</persName>
                    prior to Jim’s meetings with <persName corresp="#p_SE_1">Shevardnadze</persName>
                    in New York. The proposed NSD at Tab A reflects the results of the New York
                    meetings and our agreement on how best to proceed on the remaining <gloss
                        target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> issues in a way that will protect U.S.
                    national security interests while making every effort to complete both treaties
                    this year.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">RECOMMENDATION</p>
                <p>That you sign the proposed National Security Directive at Tab A.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d164fn2">See <ref target="#d165">Document 165</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
